Diagnosis. Male palp with VTA and RTA, VTA stout, RTA with a small basal apophysis, bulb without apophysis, embolus short, nail-shaped (
Figs 11 c–e, g
). Female epigyne with small arched sclerotized plate; copulatory ducts short; spermathecae globular (
Figs 11 f, h, i
).

Variation. Total length: males: 2.80–3.20 (n = 41 ); females: 2.90–3.80 . (n = 128 ). Some specimens have a large “n”-shaped black marking on the dorsal shield of prosoma while it is completely dark in others (
Figs 11 a, b
). The abdominal markings vary in size.
